Interface List

All Known Implementing Classes:
ArrayList, LinkedList
public interface List

A List represents an ordered collection (also known as a sequence) of elements in a container, which offers the user precise control over where in this list each element is inserted.

Parameters:

shiftLeft

void shiftLeft(int k)
Shifts the elements in this list left by k positions, and fill the vacated k slots at the end with null. The size of this list is decreased by k, and The elements originally in the first k slots are lost.

Parameters:
k - number of positions to shift
Throws:
RuntimeException - if k > size
